672-727. Two giant Trojan brothers, Pandarus and Bitias, opened the gate of the defences, scornfully bid- ding the enemy come within. Eagerly the Rutulians pressea' in, only to be slain by one or other of the two ‚· and soon the T rojans issued forth themselves into the open.
